{"cursor":"9803","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"An 'electronic visual display' is display technology which incorporates flat\npanel displays, performs as a video display, output device for presentation of\nimages transmitted electronically, for visual reception, without producing a\npermanent record.\n\nCommon applications for electronic visual displays used to be television sets or\ncomputer monitors, but these days electronic visual displays tend to be\nubiquitous as interface for large amounts of visual information in mobile\ncomputing applications like portable information communication technology\ndevices. They can also be found in digital signage.\n","linknr":156,"url":"Electronic_visual_display","recorded":1362684438,"links":16,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Display devices"],"headings":["Classification","Display mode of observation","Layout of picture elements","Emission and control of colors","Addressing modes","Display driving modes","References","Literature","See also"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Display_technology","Flat_panel_display","Video_display","Output_device","Visual","Television_set","Computer_monitor","Mobile_computing","Information_communication_technology","Digital_signage","Backlight","Electronic_paper","Cathode_ray_tube","Field_emission_display","Vacuum_fluorescent_display","Surface-conduction_electron-emitter_display","Nixie_tube","Plasma_display","Numitron","Split-flap_display","Flip-disc_display","Digital_micromirror_device","Interferometric_modulator_display","Video_projector","Rear_projection_TV","Transflective_liquid_crystal_display","Virtual_retinal_display","Head-mounted_display","Laser_projectors","Acousto-optic_modulator","Seven-segment_display","Fourteen-segment_disp